“activity  relating  to  allied  health”  means  any  activity  which 
has  a  direct  or  an  indirect  effect  on  patient  care,  or  on  the  health 
of  an  individual  or  the  population;

“profession  of  allied  health”  means  any  profession   which  has 
a  direct  or  an  indirect  effect  on  patient  care,  or  on  the  health  of 
an  individual  or  the  population;

(c)  who  has  not  applied  to  the  Registrar  for  a  renewal  of 
practising certificate for a lapse of six years continuously; 
and

(a)  he  has  attended  specialized  training  relating  to  his  Allied 
Health  Profession  in  a  recognized  training  institution  as 
may  be  determined  by  the  Council;

(a)  make any false claim in any advertisement, journal, article, 
pamphlet,  website  or  media  commercial  in  respect  of  the 
allied health services or any matter relating to health;

(a)  shall  not  practise  or  carry  on  or  operate,  or  hold  himself 
out  as  practising  or  carrying  on  or  operating,  or  take  up 
employment,  as  a  registered  practitioner;

(d)  shall  not  use  or  display  any  sign,  card  or  other  device 
representing or implying that he is a registered practitioner; 
or

or  causing  to  be  made,  or  producing  or  causing  to  be 
produced,  a  false  or  fraudulent  declaration,  certificate, 
application  or  representation;

(b)  take  or  use  any  name,  title,  addition  or  description             
implying  that  he  is  a  registered  practitioner  or  that  he 
is  recognized  by  law  as  a  registered  practitioner;

(iii)  any other offence punishable  with imprisonment,  whether  in 
itself  only  or  in  addition  to  or  in  lieu  of  a  fine,  for  more 
than  two  years;
